# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   See https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/issues/530
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to Pipfile.lock, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, it might be better to exclude it.
#   https://pipenv.pypa.io/en/latest/advanced/#pipfile-vs-pipfile-lock
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock can be included or excluded.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock can be included or excluded.
#   https://pdm.fming.dev/latest/usage/project/#commit-the-lockfile
#pdm.lock

